msgctxt "2772_望月京子：源氏名"
msgid "Hi! It's nice to meet you!"
msgstr "¡Hola! ¡Encantada de conocerle!"

msgctxt "2784_Tanimura"
msgid "You've got a pretty voice."
msgstr "Tienes una linda voz."

msgctxt "2796_望月京子：源氏名"
msgid "Thank you! Actually, I'm in a band."
msgstr "Oh, ¡gracias! De hecho, toco en una banda."

msgctxt "2808_Tanimura"
msgid "Wow. You're the singer then, huh?"
msgstr "Vaya. Entonces eres la cantante, ¿no?"

msgctxt "2820_望月京子：源氏名"
msgid "Yep. Do you like music?"
msgstr "Sí. ¿Le gusta la música?"

msgctxt "2832_Tanimura"
msgid "Well, I listen to the racing report more than music."
msgstr "No tanto, suelo escuchar más el informe de carreras que música."

msgctxt "2844_望月京子：源氏名"
msgid "Oh, I see. Not a big music fan then, huh?"
msgstr "Ah, ya veo. No es muy fanático de la música entonces."

msgctxt "2856_望月京子：源氏名"
msgid "You have to be a pretty good talker if you want to be a hostess. You have to be able to guide the conversation where you want it to go."
msgstr "Una tiene que ser muy buena charlando si quiere ser una hostess. Debe de ser capaz de dirigir la conversación hacia donde lo desea."

msgctxt "2868_Tanimura"
msgid "That's true. You've got to be a good listener, too."
msgstr "Eso es cierto. También tienes que saber escuchar a los clientes."

msgctxt "2880_望月京子：源氏名"
msgid "Well anyway, I'm a pretty good talker. In fact, I've never lost an argument."
msgstr "Sí, de todos modos soy buena charlando. De hecho, nunca perdí en una discusión."

msgctxt "2892_Tanimura"
msgid "You have arguments with your customers?"
msgstr "¿Sueles discutir con tus clientes?"

msgctxt "2904_望月京子：源氏名"
msgid "I can be a little hotheaded, so if some guy tries to harass me, he gets more than he bargained for."
msgstr "Me enojo rápido, así que si un tipo intenta pasarse de la raya, termina llevándose una sorpresa."

msgctxt "2916_Tanimura"
msgid "Shouldn't you just call one of the attendants?"
msgstr "¿No deberías solo llamar a alguno de los asistentes?"

msgctxt "2928_望月京子：源氏名"
msgid "Do you drink much at home, Tanimura-san?"
msgstr "Do you drink much at home, Tanimura-san?"

msgctxt "2940_Tanimura"
msgid "I prefer going out to drink. It suits me better."
msgstr "I prefer going out to drink. It suits me better."

msgctxt "2952_望月京子：源氏名"
msgid "I get that. Even if you go alone to a bar, having the bartender there to talk to can make a big difference."
msgstr "I get that. Even if you go alone to a bar, having the bartender there to talk to can make a big difference."

msgctxt "2964_Tanimura"
msgid "I like lively places like this. The noisier the better. It helps me relax somehow."
msgstr "I like lively places like this. The noisier the better. It helps me relax somehow."

msgctxt "2976_望月京子：源氏名"
msgid "That's a pretty cool thing to say. You're welcome to come here anytime you want a drink."
msgstr "That's a pretty cool thing to say. You're welcome to come here anytime you want a drink."

msgctxt "2988_Tanimura"
msgid "Thanks."
msgstr "Gracias."

msgctxt "3000_Himeka"
msgid "The dialogue will end after one round if you've\\r\n"\n"entered a club more than once. Please report when this message is displayed."
msgstr "El diálogo terminará después de una ronda\\r\n"\n"cuando entre al club más de una vez. Contacte a un programador si ve este mensaje."

msgctxt "3012_望月京子：源氏名"
msgid "Tanimura cannot request Kyoko.\\r\n"\n"Notify programmer if this message is displayed."
msgstr "Tanimura cannot request Kyoko.\\r\n"\n"Notify programmer if this message is displayed."

msgctxt "3024_望月京子：源氏名"
msgid "Tanimura cannot request Kyoko.\\r\n"\n"Notify programmer if this message is displayed."
msgstr "Tanimura cannot request Kyoko.\\r\n"\n"Notify programmer if this message is displayed."

msgctxt "3036_望月京子：源氏名"
msgid "Cheers!"
msgstr "¡Salud!"

msgctxt "3048_Player"
msgid "Cheers."
msgstr "Salud."

msgctxt "3060_Attendant"
msgid "That's just your imagination."
msgstr "That's just your imagination."

msgctxt "3072_Attendant"
msgid "Don't go spreading that around."
msgstr "Don't go spreading that around."

msgctxt "3084_Attendant"
msgid "You talk a lot, don't you?"
msgstr "You talk a lot, don't you?"

msgctxt "3096_Attendant"
msgid "Do you talk to spirits or something?"
msgstr "Do you talk to spirits or something?"

msgctxt "3108_Attendant"
msgid "Sorry, but you got that one wrong."
msgstr "Sorry, but you got that one wrong."

msgctxt "3120_Attendant"
msgid "You might be right, actually."
msgstr "You might be right, actually."

